# Performance

## Virtualization (@tanstack/react-virtual)

Always provide `getItemKey` for stable row identity during expand/collapse:

```typescript
const virtualizer = useVirtualizer({
  count: visibleNodeIds.length,
  getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,
  estimateSize: () => 28,
  overscan: 10,
  getItemKey: (index) => visibleNodeIds[index],
})
```

Use `scrollToIndex` to bring items into view programmatically (search matches, breadcrumb navigation).

## Web Workers

- Payloads >5MB parse in the Web Worker
- Always add a request ID to prevent stale responses from overwriting newer results
- Transfer large data as `ArrayBuffer` (zero-copy) instead of structured clone
- Keep `jsonrepair` fallback in the worker too

## Search at Scale

- Build a pre-lowercased search index during parse (avoid `.toLowerCase()` per search)
- Only auto-expand ancestors of the active match, not all matches
- For 50k+ nodes, run search in the Web Worker
- Wrap result-setting in `startTransition`

## General

- Profile before optimizing — use React DevTools Profiler and `performance.mark/measure`
- Avoid creating intermediate state updates in loops (batch into single action)
- Don't add heavy dependencies — bundle budget is 120KB gzipped
